data.author: Mostafa Gomaa
data.message:
[pddl_parser] account for pddl-constants while replacing ground params

For an atomic (aka, Ground) predicate representing an action's precond or effect,
Ground.params[i] stores the indices of the predicate's parameter values (in reference to
domain.types). When the parameter is a constant, a negative value is stored
Ground.params[i]. The value refers to the index of the constant (in
reference to domain.types.constants).

This commit, properly retrieves the constant value when grounding the
actions preconds and effects. Handling constants used to cause a
segfault.

Replace runtime errors w/ BT::NodeStatus::FAILURE

the behavior tree, or by replanning at a higher level of plansys2.

Additional functionality has also been added to allow derived classes
to cause `tick()` to return `BT::NodeStatus::FAILURE` by setting
`return_failure_` to false, providing an alternative to throwing a
runtime error.
